#   GET tickets: checkout / fetch / view / search

`be get` fetches, checks out, and indexes a version/branch/project (with `be head` as its dry-run). Tickets below close gaps in `be://` store resolution and wire-fetch sizing/dedup. Each entry is one active ticket with its live state; an entry drops off once the whole ticket lands (landed commits stay on the board's GET line). The fix-and-land method is [Issues].

##  Active tickets

 -  [GET-009] — efficient beagle↔beagle (`be://`) sync umbrella: replace `WIRE.c`'s byte-offset watermark with object-level reachability serving (`closure(wants) − closure(haves)`), cross-`file_id` serving, and a redundant-pack GC/compaction for already-bloated shards. St.1 ([[GET-007]] latest-copy) landed; St.2-4 open.

 -  [GET-014] — head/get/patch against a divergent ticket remote silently reset local trunk `?` to the fetched commit (non-ff), dropping four landed commits; a dry-run/fetch must never move `?` non-ff. Recovered via `be put '?#<sha>'` (`be get [--force]` won't move a divergent ref). Needs a clean repro to pin the verb.

 -  [GET-016] — `be get` is non-atomic for the wt: the ref/wtlog advance (COMMIT POINT, `GET.c:1338`) precedes the non-crash-safe wt write, so a partial run (or any ref-advance-without-checkout) drifts the tree; the baseline↔target delta is then empty → no-op skip leaves stale bytes, and `--force`/`get!` keys off the dirty bucket not the no-op one so it can't full-reset. Plan: (1) all-or-nothing wt GET, (2) `get!` re-examines every file + full tree reset. Sibling stuck-ref symptom may split to GET-017.

